HEADWORD: Unpursed
<hw>Un*pursed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>purse</ets> + <ets>-ed</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Robbed of a purse, or of money.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Pollock.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Taken from the purse; expended.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unqualify</ent>⟦br⟧
